<Content>Great Family Vacation Our family of 4 (kids 12 and 9) wanted a warm getaway for the holidays from cold Japan. After researching the many hotels, we decided on the Intercontinental. I am somewhat of a germophobe, so choosing a hotel is a bit stressful for me :). The hotel was beautifully decorated and we enjoyed the charm of the archetecture. Our rooms came with 2 free adult breakfasts each day at the Olive Tree. We ate there each morning of our 10 day stay. It was lovely!The rooms were nothing fancy, but we stayed in a standard room- I believe the shophouse rooms might be an upgrade. Our bathroom was beautiful and the room was extremely clean. We are not world travelers as we take 1-2 big trips a year as a family. This hotel was very nice, but not a resort. The kids were a bit disappointed with the pool area. Although the lounging chairs were nice, the water was ice-cold. It also looked as if the pool needed an update. This was not a big deal as we didn't spend much time at the hotel- we were busy enjoying all Singapore and the outlying islands had to offer.The only real complaint I had was that the lounge area was off-limits unless you purchased a drink or meal. On Christmas Eve, my family was on our way back to the room, but decided to sit in the lounge for a few minutes before heading up, to enjoy the beautiful holiday decorations. Most of the tables were open, but even so, we were asked to leave if we were not going to purchase anything. Although this wasn't a big deal, as a paying customer, I felt like if there were open tables, we should have been allowed to sit there for 5 minutes. We would stay at this hotel again as it was beautiful, clean, and in a fabulous location. 
