<Content>Fantastic Inter Continental Singapore Just returned from the Singapore Inter Continental on Dec. 1, 2008.There are two types of room you can book, either a tower room or a shop house room. I prefer the tower room. I have stayed at this property 4 times already, and each time I am very satisfied with the quality or the service, staff, and the room. Everything is 5 star, clean, and well kept up. The Tower rooms have been updated in the last 2 years with new flat panel TV's, Carpet and furnishings. Try to get a corner room if possible. Nice layout.The Shop house rooms I find to be a bit noise, because they are closer to the street. I did visit the club lounge which was just re-opend 6 months ago after an extensive renovation. I just went to look at it, because I did not pay extra for access. The Club is Beautiful! It is not cheap to stay in the club, but definitely worth the splurge if you are so inclined. I Paid 220 Singapore Dollars per night ( Leisure weekend rate) which came with a lovely buffet breakfast each morning. The Breakfast is 5 star. Great food, and great professional service. You can drink all the fresh Cappucino you want included in price. Many Many dishes to chose from at the buffet table. I highly recommend this hotel. The Location is fantastic. It is in the center of Singapore, and a short ( $3.00 US Dollar) cab ride to the orchard road shopping area. Although there is plenty of good sight seeing and shopping right outside your door. The staff is extremely responsive to all guests needs. The Lobby area is beautiful white marble throughout, with high high ceilings and floor to ceiling windows. They have a piano playing at night during cocktail hour and high tea. The hotel is extremely well kept, and extremely clean. Beds are very comfortable with huge down pillows. Great Mattress, Flat Panel LCD and I Pod docking. 
